title: DAI Proposal Vote
body:
### **How should the 168,763 DAI generated from the Balancer Liquidity Pool and the Uniswap v2 pool be used?**

After a week of [discussion and signature gathering](https://forum.hoprnet.org/c/hopr-dao-v0-2/dai-proposals/64), seven proposals reached the 15% threshold needed to progress to a vote.

Click any of the proposal titles below to read a proposal in full. Please read all the proposals and then vote for your favourite. Your voting power is equal to the HOPR tokens controlled by your connected address (including HOPR, xHOPR, wxHOPR and xHOPR in our [staking program](stake.hoprnet.org), but not tokens in CEXs or liquidity pools).

You can assign your voting power however you like, among any number of options. **Results will be calculated quadratically.**

The seven proposals are:

- PROPOSAL #2: [Incentivized creativity contest after HOPR mainnet network launch (building on top of HOPR)](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-2-incentivized-creativity-contest-after-hopr-mainnet-network-launch-building-on-top-of-hopr/3258)

- PROPOSAL #3: [DAO approved grants for dapp development](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-3-dao-approved-grants-for-dapp-development/3259)

- PROPOSAL #6: [Grant program + Incentives for node runners & hodlers](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-6-grant-program-incentives-for-node-runners-hodlers/3269)

- PROPOSAL #7: [Transfer funds to the HOPR Association to hire additional staff](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-7-transfer-funds-to-the-hopr-association-to-hire-additional-staff/3270)

- PROPOSAL #10: [Support strong holders and node runners through HOPR hardware device free distribution](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-10-support-strong-holders-and-node-runners-through-hopr-hardware-device-free-distribution/3275)

- PROPOSAL #12 [Buy back HOPR from the market and distribute among the participants of the staking program](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-12-buyback-hopr-from-the-market-and-distribution-among-the-participants-of-the-staking-program/3280)

- PROPOSAL #14 [DAI Proposals to be used in line with HOPR Token Proposals](https://forum.hoprnet.org/t/proposal-14-dai-proposals-to-be-used-in-line-with-hopr-token-proposals/3346)
